<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-01T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-01T05:00:00-05:00" n="120" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">660F.116/176: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wright</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-01T11:00:00+01:00">August 1, 1935—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 1—9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>30. My despatch No. 206, June 25.<note n="23" xml:id="d120fn23">Not
                                    printed.</note> Government decree published today effective
                                August 1–October 31 reduces import duty lard to 200 crowns and
                                fatbacks to 150 crowns per 100 kilos. Alleged discrimination
                                referred to in your instruction 67 is being investigated.</p>
                            <p>Please inform Commerce.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>